title: For Sale:  SOUTH CAROLINA CONCEALED WEAPONS PERMIT COURSE
postcontent:
SC Concealed Weapons Permit Courses for the month of August are Saturday August 9th, 16th, 23rd, 30th, 2014, from 9am to 430pm hosted by Blue Ridge Shooting Sports at 1310 W Wade Hampton Blvd, Greer, SC, 29651. The course cost $50. You need to bring your firearm, 50 rounds of ammo, and a belt with holster. There are 10 slots available per course, to ensure yourself a spot you can preregister by going to WWW.BLUERIDGEFIREARMSTRAINING.COM and sign up via the registration form and paypal. We will call when confirmation is received. SEE BELOW FOR MORE INFO. Thanks for your business.

Course Requirements

#1. Absolutely no charges/convictions for any Felonies, Criminal Domestic Violence, Drugs, or any misdemeanors that carry more than 2+ years imprisonment / probation or any charge that would prohibit you from owning or possessing a firearm. If found NOT GUILTY you should still be eligible. If you are unsure about your status you can contact SLED at REDACTED for clarification.

#2. All necessary paperwork and finger printing will be provided by me. Make sure that the address on your SC drivers license matches your current address. If not SLED will send the application back.

#3. Wear a tight neck shirt, no collared shirts please. Also bring a ball cap guys and girls. All other protective gear (safety glasses and hearing protection) will be provided by me. If you want to bring your own protective gear that is fine as well.

#4. Have a holster with at least 1 level of retention. This means a type of holster with a strap, snap, or button that secures the handgun from being pulled from the holster without being unsecured first. You must wear long pants with a belt. 

#5. Bring a small to medium caliber handgun with 50 rounds of ammunition, .22 cal, .32cal, .380cal, .38cal, 9mm, .40cal, .45cal. No derringer or magnum high caliber pistols please. If you do not currently own a firearm, speak with me prior to the class and arrangements can be made to borrow one. You will still be responsible for the ammo for the borrowed firearm.

#6. The total cost of the course is $100. This needs to be separated as such, $50. cash/card for the instructor, and a $50. cashiers check or money order made out to SLED DATA CENTER CWP. You do not need to have the SLED fee the day of the class, only when you get ready to mail the application off. SLED will not accept personal checks or cash.


Most important is safety, Know your firearm prior to class, if you need to practice to familiarize yourself with your firearm or to schedule a class, call me at REDACTED or REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  Buffalo Bore Ammo - 9X18 Makarov +P Ammo - 115 gr. Hard Cast - FN (1,000 fps/ME 255 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
http://www.armslist.com/posts/b6d2bc8655b74ae383aa64956ac0a816/edit?stage=Info

Our introduction of a "heavy bullet for cartridge" 9X18 Makarov +P loading is the sole result of numerous customer requests.  With millions of these pistols now on American soil and no +P heavy loadings available, this cartridge and the many pistol owners are suffering from the lack of serious fight stopping ammunition.  This load is 20grs. heavier and 100 fps faster than standard 9X18 ammo.

This loading features a flash suppressed powder, so if you need to shoot in low light, you won't be blinded by your own gun fire and this is a useful tactical advantage since around 95% of all civilian shootings in the US happen in low light while the criminal element is out and about.  Our use of a hard cast bullet, with a flat nose, can best be understood if you'll read our technical article on "The Use of Expanding Bullets in Small Defensive Cartridges," posted under the "Technical Articles" category on our home page.

Further, please note that the use of hard cast bullets (not lead but, Hard Cast) does NOT cause lead fouling in the polygonal rifling's used in all 9X18 Makarov pistols.  For more information, please see our technical articles entitled "Hard Cast Bullets in Polygonal Barrels" and "Dangers of Pure Lead Cowboy Bullets". We found no appreciable leading in any of our Makarov test guns. It should also be noted that all of our test guns functioned and fed flawlessly with this load. We also experienced very good to excellent accuracy in all test guns.

Please note the real world velocities listed below from real world 9X18 Makarov pistols. At Buffalo Bore we always use real, ‘over-the-counter’ firearms for our published velocities, as we feel the use of laboratory test barrels that give false, high velocities does the customer a disservice as each customer needs to know what their carry ammo will really do on-the-street in a real world situation.

As long as it's in good operating condition, the stock and forearm aren't cracked, the barrel is clean, and the action is tight.   If the price I have on here is a little low for what you have to offer,...send me some pictures of it...I can come up some on the offer.

If you live out of state,...and the deal is a good one,..for a GOOD offer,...I'll pay all FFL fees to ship.
